Mystery Bitcoin creator ‘discovered’
His true identy has been shrouded in mystery for years, but now, possibly, he may have been uncovered.
Known as “the father of Bitcoin”, the digital currency worth billions, Satoshi Nakamoto appeared to vanish in 2010 when he stopped responding to all messages from Bitcoin’s early adherents.
Since then, wild theories have spread in the digital world about his existence. Some believed his name was the pseudonym for a whizkid hacker based in Tokyo. Others believed it was the name of a collective of computer programmers. Nobody has claimed to have met him in person.
But according to a report, he is a 64-year-old Japanese immigrant living in a small town in California. He has been described as a “amazing physicist” who worked on secret US government projects, and who spends his days tending to his passion for model train sets.
